inputDataLabel: Data label of the file used as an input
outputDataLabel: Data label of the file generated as an output
varId: Unique id of the output variable

name: daily_nodata_filter_s
comment: Bit, position 1: hasNoInput, 2: neuralCloud, 3, backgroundReflectance nodata, 4: rareObservation, 5: STC cloud, 6: Cloud extension, 7: Saltpan and isolated. Default value: 1 for absent file or corrupted file.

name: daily_zero_filter_s
comment: Bit, position 1: NeuralOther excluding state_1km.clouds and including state_1km.saltpans, 2: NDSIBelowMinus005, 3: rawSnowBelow10, 4: rawGrainBelow40, 5: lowElevation, 6: waterBody, 7: rawSnowEquals0

name: sensor_and_solar_azimuth_sensor_mask
comment: Bit, position 1: sensor_azimuth nodata, 2: sensor_azimuth too low, 3: sensor_azimuth too high. 4: solar_azimuth nodata, 5: solar_azimuth too low, 6: solar_azimuth too high.

name: sensor_and_solar_zenith_sensor_mask
comment: Bit, position 1: sensor_zenith nodata, 2: sensor_zenith too low, 3: sensor_zenith too high. 4: solar_zenith nodata, 5: solar_zenith too low, 6: solar_zenith too high.

name: reflectance_1_7_sensor_mask
comment: Bit, position 1: reflectance_1 nodata, 2: reflectance_1 too low, 3: reflectance_1 too high. 4: reflectance_2 nodata, 5: reflectance_2 too low, 6: reflectance_2 too high, 7: reflectance_3 nodata, etcâ€¦

name: grain_size_and_dust_mask
comment: fsca below value â†’ spat interp grain size and idem dust

name: daily_grain_size_dust_s
comment: Bit, position 1: spatial interpolation of grain size, 2: grain size nodata because below min, 3: grain size nodata because above max, 4: spatial interpolation of dust concentration, 5: dust concentration nodata because below min, 6: dust concentration nodata because above max.
